I ultimately came down to a no-vote (neutral vote) on this.

I think the main problem here is that the core concept leans heavily on a few site cliches, and doesn't do enough to build beyond that. As a fan of technical scips, the tight tone and some interesting nuances to the effect helped sell me a bit on the idea (the experiment logs in particular have some good moments of black humor and creepiness), but ultimately there's no moment where I find myself saying  or staring at the screen processing the full ramifications of what I just read.

I'm not saying this can't work, but it might be one to put on the back-burner while you work on something more off the beaten trail; some of the best twists come from letting an idea sit for a while until you get one of those  moments.







